# 3. 届いた声

KAITO: That was great, everyone!
KAITO: Miku, Rin, you both looked really cute during that dance routine! Len, you exuded a princely aura! Lastly, MEIKO, Luka, I was blown away by your singing performance!
KAITO: You all shined so much that I don't think we'll need to use any lights!
Miku: Really? That's wonderful to hear...!
Len: I appreciate the praise, but I feel a little embarrassed now.
Rin: Minori and the others aren't gonna know what to do with themselves!
Luka: Yes, I doubt they will. Still...
Luka: We can't be satisfied with just this.
MEIKO & Rin: What?
Luka: Miku, I think you can look even cuter and act yourself more during your solo when you're dancing on center stage.
Luka: Rin, Len, you two could jump out in front and interact with the audience more. MEIKO, we need to synchronize our movements better.
Luka: Finally, KAITO, you should join us for this next one! It just doesn't feel the same if all six of us aren't involved.
Miku: Luka...!
KAITO: Yes... It would be nice to spread hope with all of you.
KAITO: Then, give me a minute to get ready...!
Luka: Okay, we'll be waiting.
Rin: Don't be too long!
MEIKO: In the meantime, why don't we go through that dance routine again?
Rin: Yeah, let's really get it down!
Luka: (I don't normally say things like what I just did...)
Luka: (But I couldn't help myself... I really want to show Minori and the others that we're there for them.)
Luka: (Still...)
Luka: (We all feel the same way about that, don't we...?)
Luka: (Of course we do. They're wonderful girls who always do their best for the sake of others...)
Luka: (Not only that...)
Luka: (We all want them to keep advancing towards their goal.)
Luka: Which means I need to keep doing my best to support them...
Luka: Hm? What is this...?
Luka: Wait, huh...?
Miku: “I'm gonna try, master! I'm gonna use this energy to make everyone smile...!”
Miku: (To make everyone smile...)
Miku: (I'm so glad Emu and the others are gonna get to keep pursuing their dreams together...!)
Miku: (Don't ever let their smiles fade away...)
Miku: “Please...!”
MEIKO: Nice practice, everyone!! You all did a wonderful job!
Len: Yeah! Especially you, Miku! You really gave it your all there!
Rin: I started tearing up during the final scene☆
Rin: Oh...
Rin: Oh nooo! She's crying again!
Len: You're going a little overboard, Miku!
MEIKO: It's quite impressive that you cry every time we practice.
Miku: *Cry* But! But!
Miku: All these emotions well up inside of me when I think about the others! I can't stop myself from crying!
Miku: Still, I know I need to keep it together when we do this for real! Because I'm gonna cast a spell on all of them!
???: You can do it!
Miku: Huh?
Len: What's wrong, Miku?
Miku: I, uhh... I thought I heard someone's voice just now!
Miku: I feel like we're being watched...
Rin: What?
KAITO: By who? Tsukasa and the others aren't supposed to be here yet.
Miku: Hmm... Maybe it was just my imagination...
MEIKO: Then, why don't we do another run-through before they get here?
Rin: Yeah☆ And let's get the lights all set up like we're doing this for real!
Miku: Oh, good idea! Let's do that!
Miku: Wait, just now...!
MEIKO: I think... They heard you, Miku!
Rin: Whoa! That's amazing! How'd you do that?!
Miku: I-I'm not sure... They were all doing their best, so I just...
Luka: Hehe. I think I understand how you feel, Miku. I also wish I could show my support for everyone in each SEKAI sometimes.
MEIKO: Me too... If only there were a way for us to do that.
KAITO: Huh? Did something flash just now...?
Len: Hey, there's something over here!
Luka: Oh, you're right. It looks like a ball of light.
MEIKO: Huh? Wait, isn't this...?
Miku: *Gasp*
